      passage: `The unique subak water management system used to irrigate the rice paddy fields of the Indonesian island of Bali has a rich cultural, philosophical, and historical significance dating back to the ninth century. The many elements of subak&mdash;terraces, canals, and water temples&mdash;are ______: they are joined together into a single cohesive unit.`,
